<p>I'm having some problem with my code, the last error is replace only some html elements have <em>overflow: hidden;</em> to <em>overflow: none;</em>, i can use javascript or css to do it, but i don't know how at this time. Please help me!</p>  <p><strong>Is there anyway to select elements that have css style</strong> <em>overflow: hidden;</em> <strong>in javascript or css?</strong></p>  <p><strong>UPDATE 2: (everything came ok!)</strong></p>  <p>Thanks <strong>Pranav C Balan</strong>, <strong>Michael_B</strong> have gave some awesome answers.</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-js lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>var ele = $('.selector').filter(function() {   return $(this).css('overflow') == 'hidden'; })  ele.css('color', 'red');</code></pre> <pre class="snippet-code-css lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>.overflow {   overflow: hidden }</code></pre> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.1/jquery.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;div class=selector&gt;1&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="selector overflow"&gt;2&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=selector style="overflow:hidden"&gt;3&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=selector&gt;1&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="selector overflow"&gt;4&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=selector&gt;5&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>